‌Mission planning

  • Using a mission planning app is essential to get uniform/desired image spacing


  • If you ever try getting imagery without a mission planning app… it will look like the pilot was

    ‌Mission planning

    • Several options are available, consider which is best for your needs


      ‌Mission planning

    • Considerations before choosing an app

      • Compatibility with device, UAS, cameras

      • Mission resume, repeatability

      • Flexibility vs. ease of use

      • Probability of error


    • Most are free or inexpensive… try several!


    • When buying equipment, ask the sales representative about recommendations for your combination of aircraft, device, cameras, and project requirements


      ‌Mission planning

    • Trade-offs

      • Higher altitude=more area/time, but lower resolution.

        ‌Mission planning

    • Trade-offs

      • Higher overlap increases stitching quality, but reduces area/time

      • Ideal overlap depends on mapped surface



        Altitude: 80m; Overlap: 75/85; Time: 4m 12s


        Altitude: 80m; Overlap: 70/70; Time: 3m 11s
